    "ax = plt.gca()\n",
    "ax.set_aspect('equal', adjustable='box')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We now estimate $\\pi$ by using the length of the number points in the circle and in the quarter as approximation to their area."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 257,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "We estimate the value of pi to be: 3.28.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Let us estimate pi\n",
    "pi_est = 4 * (len(in_circle) / len(in_square))    \n",
    "print('We estimate the value of pi to be: ' + str(pi_est) + '.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now with a few runs, we do not get a good answer. \n",
    "\n",
    "In fact, a Monte Carlo approach needs more runs to **converge**. \n",
    "\n",
    "You should explore how changing the number of runs changes your estimate of $\\pi$ (and how your calculation converges)."
   ]
